Name: ActiveViewCpm
Notes: Average cost of viewable impressions (ActiveViewImpressions).

Name: ActiveViewCtr
Notes: How often people clicked your ad after it became viewable. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: ActiveViewImpressions
Notes: How often your ad has become viewable on a Display Network site.

Name: ActiveViewMeasurability
Notes: The ratio of impressions that could be measured by Active View over the number of served impressions. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: ActiveViewMeasurableCost
Notes: The cost of the impressions you received that were measurable by Active View.

Name: ActiveViewMeasurableImpressions
Notes: The number of times your ads are appearing on placements in positions where they can be seen.

Name: ActiveViewViewability
Display Name: Active View viewable impr. / measurable impr.
Notes: The percentage of time when your ad appeared on an Active View enabled site (measurable impressions) and was viewable (viewable impressions). To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: AdGroupId
Notes: The ID of the AdGroup.

Name: AdGroupName
Notes: The name of the AdGroup.

Name: AdNetworkType1
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / unknown
SEARCH / Search Network
CONTENT / Display Network
YOUTUBE_SEARCH / YouTube Search
YOUTUBE_WATCH / YouTube Videos
MIXED / Cross-network
Notes: First level network type.

Name: AdNetworkType2
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / unknown
SEARCH / Google search
SEARCH_PARTNERS / Search partners
CONTENT / Display Network
YOUTUBE_SEARCH / YouTube Search
YOUTUBE_WATCH / YouTube Videos
MIXED / Cross-network
Notes: Second level network type (includes search partners).

Name: AverageCost
Notes: The average amount you pay per interaction. This amount is the total cost of your ads divided by the total number of interactions.

Name: AverageCpc
Notes: The total cost of all clicks divided by the total number of clicks received.

Name: AverageCpm
Notes: Average Cost-per-thousand impressions (CPM).

Name: AveragePosition
Notes: Your ad's position relative to those of other advertisers. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: CampaignId
Notes: The ID of the Campaign.

Name: CampaignName
Notes: The name of the Campaign.

Name: Clicks
Notes: The number of clicks.

Name: ConversionRate
Notes: The number of conversions divided by total clicks that can be tracked to conversions. Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: Conversions
Notes: The number of conversions for all conversion actions that you have opted into optimization. This field is formatted with dot (".") for decimal separator, precision of two decimal positions and no thousands separator (e.g. 1000000.00). To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: ConversionValue
Notes: The sum of conversion values for all conversions. This field is formatted with dot (".") for decimal separator, precision of two decimal positions and no thousands separator (e.g. 1000000.00). To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: Cost
Notes: The sum of your cost-per-click (CPC) and cost-per-thousand impressions (CPM) costs during this period.

Name: CostPerConversion
Notes: The Cost attributable to conversion-tracked clicks divided by the number of conversions

Name: Ctr
Notes: The number of clicks your ad receives (Clicks) divided by the number of times your ad is shown (Impressions). Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: Date
Notes: The date formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.

Name: DayOfWeek
Enum Values:
MONDAY / Monday
TUESDAY / Tuesday
WEDNESDAY / Wednesday
THURSDAY / Thursday
FRIDAY / Friday
SATURDAY / Saturday
SUNDAY / Sunday
Notes: The name of the day of the week, e.g., "Monday".

Name: Device
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / Other
DESKTOP / Computers
HIGH_END_MOBILE / Mobile devices with full browsers
TABLET / Tablets with full browsers
Notes: Device type where the impression was shown.

Name: ExpandedFinalUrlString
Notes: The final URL with ValueTrack parameters replaced with their final rendered values.

Name: Impressions
Notes: Count of how often your ad has appeared on a search results page or website on the Google Network.

Name: InteractionRate
Notes: How often people interact with your ad after it is shown to them. This is the number of interactions divided by the number of times your ad is shown. Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: Interactions
Notes: The number of interactions. An interaction is the main user action associated with an ad format--clicks for text and shopping ads, views for video ads, and so on.

Name: InteractionTypes
Notes: The types of interactions that are reflected in the Interactions, InteractionRate, and AverageCost columns.

Name: Month
Notes: The first day of the month, formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.

Name: MonthOfYear
Enum Values:
JANUARY / January
FEBRUARY / February
MARCH / March
APRIL / April
MAY / May
JUNE / June
JULY / July
AUGUST / August
SEPTEMBER / September
OCTOBER / October
NOVEMBER / November
DECEMBER / December
Notes: The name of the month of the year, e.g., "December".

Name: Quarter
Notes: The first day of the quarter, formatted as yyyy-MM-dd. Uses the calendar year for quarters, e.g., the second quarter of 2014 starts on 2014-04-01.

Name: Slot
Enum Values:
SearchRhs / Google search: Side
SearchTop / Google search: Top
SearchOther / Google search: Other
Content / Google Display Network
AfsTop / Search partners: Top
AfsOther / Search partners: Other
Mixed / Cross-network
Unknown /
Notes: The position of the Ad.

Name: UnexpandedFinalUrlString
Notes: The final URL with ValueTrack parameter templates left in place.

Name: ValuePerConversion
Notes: The total value of your conversions divided by the total number of conversions. This field is formatted with dot (".") for decimal separator, precision of two decimal positions and no thousands separator (e.g. 1000000.00). To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: Week
Notes: The date for the Monday of the week, formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.

Name: Year
Notes: The year, formatted as yyyy.
